# SWIM Implementation Patterns and Best Practices

## Security Patterns

### TLS Configuration Pattern

**Requirement**: All SWIM communications must use TLS 1.2 exclusively

**Implementation**:
```
TLS Version: TLS 1.2 only
Cipher Suites:
  - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
  - ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
  - ECDHE-ECDSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
  - ECDHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384
  - DHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256
  - DHE-RSA-AES256-GCM-SHA384

Certificate Validation:
  - Verify trust path to accepted CA
  - Check certificate expiration
  - Verify certificate revocation status (CRL/OCSP)
```

**Camel Configuration Example**:
```java
SSLContextParameters sslContext = new SSLContextParameters();
KeyStoreParameters keyStore = new KeyStoreParameters();
keyStore.setResource("/secrets/client_certificate.p12");
keyStore.setPassword("***");

KeyManagersParameters keyManagers = new KeyManagersParameters();
keyManagers.setKeyStore(keyStore);
sslContext.setKeyManagers(keyManagers);

KeyStoreParameters trustStore = new KeyStoreParameters();
trustStore.setResource("/secrets/ca_certificate.pem");
TrustManagersParameters trustManagers = new TrustManagersParameters();
trustManagers.setKeyStore(trustStore);
sslContext.setTrustManagers(trustManagers);
```

**Nginx Configuration Example**:
```nginx
ssl_protocols TLSv1.2;
ssl_ciphers 'ECDHE-ECDSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256:ECDHE-RSA-AES128-GCM-SHA256:...';
ssl_prefer_server_ciphers on;
ssl_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/server_certificate.pem;
ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/ssl/server_key.pem;
ssl_trusted_certificate /etc/nginx/ssl/ca_certificate.pem;
```

