### Password Management Pattern

**Storage**: PBKDF2 with SHA256, minimum 150,000 iterations

**Validation Rules**:
- Minimum 10 characters
- Support full ASCII printable character set
- Check against known breach databases (e.g., HaveIBeenPwned with k-anonymity)
- NO mandatory character class combinations (reduces entropy)
- NO routine expiration (unless compromised)

**Implementation** (Java example):
```java
public String hashPassword(String password) {
    SecureRandom random = new SecureRandom();
    byte[] salt = new byte[16];
    random.nextBytes(salt);
    
    PBEKeySpec spec = new PBEKeySpec(
        password.toCharArray(),
        salt,
        150000,
        256
    );
    
    SecretKeyFactory factory = SecretKeyFactory.getInstance("PBKDF2WithHmacSHA256");
    byte[] hash = factory.generateSecret(spec).getEncoded();
    
    return Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(salt) + ":" +
           Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(hash);
}
```

