## Integration Patterns

### ETL Pattern for SWIM Services

**Extract**: Consume data from external sources (REST APIs, databases, files)

**Transform**: Convert to SWIM-compliant format (AIXM, FIXM, DNOTAM)

**Load**: Publish to SWIM topic or persist to database

**Camel Route Example**:
```java
from("timer:extract?period=10000")
  .to("https://api.external.com/flights")
  .unmarshal().json()
  
  .process(exchange -> {
      List<ExternalFlight> flights = exchange.getMessage().getBody(List.class);
      List<FixmFlight> fixmFlights = transformer.toFixm(flights);
      exchange.getMessage().setBody(fixmFlights);
  })
  
  .marshal().jaxb()
  .setHeader("JMSContentType", constant("application/vnd.eurocontrol.fixm+xml"))
  .to("amqps://broker:5671/topic://flights.scheduled");
```

---

### Error Handling Pattern

**Dead Letter Channel**: Route failed messages to error queue

**Retry Policy**: Exponential backoff with maximum attempts

**Camel Configuration**:
```java
errorHandler(deadLetterChannel("jms:queue:DLQ")
  .maximumRedeliveries(3)
  .redeliveryDelay(1000)
  .backOffMultiplier(2)
  .useExponentialBackOff()
  .logStackTrace(true)
  .onExceptionOccurred(new NotificationProcessor()));

from("amqps://broker:5671/queue://swim-client.notam.EBBR")
  .unmarshal().jaxb()
  .to("bean:notamProcessor")
  .to("jpa:NotamEvent");
```

---

### Idempotency Pattern

**Problem**: Duplicate message processing due to retries

**Solution**: Idempotent consumer with message ID tracking

**Camel Implementation**:
```java
from("amqps://broker:5671/queue://swim-client.arrivals.EBBR")
  .idempotentConsumer(header("JMSMessageID"))
    .messageIdRepository(new JdbcMessageIdRepository(dataSource, "processed_messages"))
  .unmarshal().json()
  .to("bean:flightProcessor")
  .to("jpa:FlightEvent");
```

