## Deployment Patterns

### Secret Injection Pattern

**Problem**: Certificates and credentials must be securely injected

**Kubernetes Solution**: Mount Secrets as files

**Deployment YAML**:
```yaml
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: dnotam-provider
spec:
  template:
    spec:
      containers:
      - name: camel-app
        image: dnotam-provider:latest
        volumeMounts:
        - name: swim-certs
          mountPath: /secrets
          readOnly: true
        env:
        - name: BROKER_HOST
          value: "amq-broker:5671"
        - name: BROKER_CERT_DB
          value: "/secrets/ca_certificate.pem"
        - name: BROKER_CERT_FILE
          value: "/secrets/client_certificate.pem"
        - name: BROKER_CERT_KEY
          value: "/secrets/client_key.pem"
      volumes:
      - name: swim-certs
        secret:
          secretName: swim-client-certs
```

---

### Conditional Component Deployment Pattern

**Use Case**: Deploy Provider, Consumer, or Both based on configuration

**Helm Values**:
```yaml
mode: "both"  # Options: "provider", "consumer", "both"

provider:
  enabled: true
  topics:
    - "notam.EBBR"
    - "notam.LFPG"

consumer:
  enabled: true
  subscriptions:
    - topic: "notam.EHAM"
      callback: "notamProcessor"
```

**Helm Template**:
```yaml
{{- if or (eq .Values.mode "provider") (eq .Values.mode "both") }}
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: {{ .Release.Name }}-provider
spec:
  # ... provider deployment spec
{{- end }}

{{- if or (eq .Values.mode "consumer") (eq .Values.mode "both") }}
apiVersion: apps/v1
kind: Deployment
metadata:
  name: {{ .Release.Name }}-consumer
spec:
  # ... consumer deployment spec
{{- end }}
```

